section.def:
advanced certificate (高級證書)—(a)means a certificate issued under section 6(4); and(b)includes—(i)a certificate mentioned in paragraph (a) as renewed under section
                            6(5); and(ii)a certificate issued under section 10 to replace a
                        certificate mentioned in subparagraph (i) or paragraph (a);

basic certificate (基本證書)—(a)means a certificate issued under section 6(3); and(b)includes—(i)a certificate mentioned in paragraph (a) as renewed under section
                            6(5); and(ii)a certificate issued under section 10 to replace a
                        certificate mentioned in subparagraph (i) or paragraph (a);

paragraph.content:
that is a ship to which the Merchant Shipping (Safety) (Construction and
                Survey) Regulation (Cap. 369 sub. leg. BD)
                applies;

that is not a ship falling within paragraph (a) of the definition of
                        specified ship in section 28(3) of that
                Regulation;

a reference to a basic certificate includes a certificate recognized under
                        section 9(1) as being equivalent to a basic certificate;
                    and

a reference to a basic certificate includes a certificate recognized under
                        section 9(1) as being equivalent to a basic certificate;
                    and

subparagraph.content:
has satisfied the requirements mentioned in subsection
                                (3)(a) or (4)(a) (as the case requires);
                            and

paragraph.content:
the details of the applicable standards of competency to be attained, or
                    the details of the applicable conditions to be satisfied, by an applicant to
                    qualify for the issue of a certificate of proficiency;

the offence of fraud under section 16A of the Theft Ordinance
                        (Cap. 210) in relation to a certificate of
                    proficiency;
